{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 File MCP Plugin \u8211- How It Works\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 \u55357?\u56513?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 File MCP Plugin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 How It Works \u8212- Complete Guide\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 MODEL CONTEXT PROTOCOL\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 1 What is the File MCP Plugin?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The {\b File MCP (Model Context Protocol) Plugin} is a powerful bridge that connects AI assistants like Claude directly to your local file system. It enables Claude to read, write, create, delete, move, and manage files and directories on your computer using natural language \u8212- without requiring any code or terminal knowledge.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b MCP} stands for {\i Model Context Protocol}, an open standard that allows AI models to securely interact with external tools, APIs, and local resources in a structured, controlled manner.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 2 Plugin Architecture\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The File MCP Plugin follows a {\b client-server model} with three main layers:\par}
