{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 3 How It Works \u8212- Step by Step\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 You Give a Command\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You type: {\i "Create a folder called RAJAREDDY_FILE_MCP on D: drive."}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Claude Understands the Intent\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Claude parses your message, identifies the intent (create directory), extracts parameters (name, location), and selects the correct MCP tool to call.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 3\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 MCP Tool is Invoked\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Claude calls {\f1 filesystem:make_directory} with {\f1 path = D:\\RAJAREDDY_FILE_MCP}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 4\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Plugin Executes the Operation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The MCP server validates the request and executes the file system operation using OS-level APIs on your machine.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 5\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Result is Returned\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The plugin returns structured metadata \u8212- success/failure, file size, timestamps \u8212- back to Claude.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 6\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Claude Reports Back\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Claude translates the result into plain English, confirming the action or explaining any errors clearly.\par}
